issues.title: Engine Oil Cooler Hose Failure
issues.description: The engine oil cooler hoses can develop leaks or rupture, leading to significant oil loss and potential engine damage. This is a known issue with the Toyota 3.5L V6 engine used in the Evora GT.
issues.fix_description: Replace the faulty oil cooler hoses with updated versions and inspect all related connections
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of engine bay for oil leaks and monitoring oil levels frequently

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Cracking
issues.description: Some owners report hairline cracks developing in carbon fiber body panels, particularly around stress points and mounting areas.
symptoms: Visible hairline cracks in carbon fiber
issues.fix_description: Professional carbon fiber repair or panel replacement by qualified technician
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes and careful handling during transport

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The door handle mechanisms can fail, making it difficult or impossible to open doors from the outside. The internal cables and springs are prone to breaking.
symptoms: Handle moves but door doesn't open
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism and associated cables
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of door handles and regular lubrication of mechanisms

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Issues
issues.description: AC compressor failures have been reported, resulting in complete loss of air conditioning function. The compressor may seize or develop internal leaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace AC compressor and associated components, evacuate and recharge system
issues.prevention: Regular AC system maintenance and use AC system regularly even in winter

issues.title: Fuel Pump Relay Problems
issues.description: Faulty fuel pump relays can cause intermittent or complete fuel pump failure, leading to engine stalling or no-start conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump relay and inspect fuel pump operation
issues.prevention: Carry spare relays and have electrical system inspected regularly

issues.title: Transmission Cooling Lines Leakage
issues.description: Transmission cooling lines can develop leaks at connection points, leading to transmission fluid loss and potential overheating.
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking cooling lines and top off transmission fluid
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service and inspection of cooling lines

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: The touchscreen infotainment system may freeze or become unresponsive, requiring a system reset to restore functionality.
issues.fix_description: Software update or system reset, may require unit replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Keep system software updated and avoid temperature extremes

issues.title: Suspension Bushings Premature Wear
issues.description: Suspension bushings, particularly rear control arm bushings, may wear prematurely causing handling issues and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn suspension bushings and perform wheel alignment
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive driving on poor road surfaces

editorial.tagline: Pure analog supercar thrills without compromise
editorial.hero_blurb: The Evora GT represents Lotus at its purest - a supercharged masterpiece that prioritizes driving purity over creature comforts. This is the final evolution of Hethel's mid-engine philosophy before the electric future.
editorial.essence: The Evora GT distills everything Lotus knows about lightweight performance into one sublime package. With Toyota's bulletproof 3.5L supercharged V6 and classic mid-engine proportions, it delivers authentic supercar thrills without the drama.
editorial.heritage: The final iteration of Lotus's mid-engine sports car lineage that began with the Europa in 1966. The Evora GT caps off a decade of refinement, representing the culmination of Colin Chapman's 'simplify and add lightness' philosophy in modern form.
editorial.design_philosophy: Pure function dictating form - every line serves aerodynamic or cooling purposes while maintaining Lotus's signature delicate proportions. The GT's aggressive aero package adds purposeful aggression without compromising the Evora's inherent elegance.
editorial.motorsport_history: Built on decades of Lotus motorsport DNA, though the Evora GT itself focused on road-going perfection rather than competition. The platform's racing variants proved the chassis's capabilities in GT4 and club racing series worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The supercharged Toyota V6 delivers linear, immediate power with a mechanical soundtrack that builds to a glorious crescendo. No turbo lag, just pure atmospheric response with supercharger whine adding musical complexity.
editorial.transmission_feel: The six-speed manual is poetry in motion - perfectly weighted throws with crisp, mechanical precision that rewards smooth technique. Each gear change feels deliberate and satisfying, connecting driver to machine.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Telepathic balance defines the Evora GT's character - neutral handling that transitions seamlessly between understeer and oversteer based purely on driver input. The chassis communicates every nuance of the road surface.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulically-assisted perfection with natural weight that varies meaningfully with speed and load. Every input is rewarded with precise response and detailed feedback about front tire grip levels.
editorial.brake_confidence: Phenomenal stopping power with perfect pedal feel and zero fade. The Brembos bite hard initially then modulate beautifully, inspiring complete confidence in threshold braking scenarios.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated symphony combining supercharger whine, intake growl, and exhaust bark. The note is purposeful rather than theatrical - more Stradivarius than Marshall stack.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who prioritize connection over convenience and understand that the best supercars aren't necessarily the fastest. Perfect for those who appreciate analog excellence and engineering artistry.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge snobs seeking status symbols or comfort-focused buyers wanting daily usability. Those expecting Italian exotic drama or German precision luxury should look elsewhere.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Evora GT is your last chance to own a truly analog supercar from one of history's greatest chassis engineers. Prices are climbing as collectors recognize this as the end of an era.
